# Managed by vigOS devkit — regenerated on upgrade; local edits are lost.
# Customize in justfile.project. Bugs / missing tools: https://github.com/vig-os/devkit/issues

# Language-neutral base .gitignore
#
# This is a MANAGED scaffold file: init-workspace.sh overwrites it on every
# upgrade and appends a per-language fragment (Python / Node / Rust) detected
# from the repo's marker files (pyproject.toml / package.json / Cargo.toml).
# Do not hand-edit durable ignores here — they will not survive an upgrade.
# Put repo-specific root ignores in .gitignore.project (preserved on upgrade);
# init-workspace.sh appends its contents here on every regeneration (#1092).

# Environments
.env
# .envrc (use flake) is committed for nix-direnv onboarding (#640); the local
# evaluation cache and any per-user overrides are not.
.direnv/
.envrc.local

# Editors / IDEs (uncomment to ignore local editor state)
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# Personal justfile recipes
justfile.local

# Pre-commit cache
.pre-commit-cache/

# process-compose / services-flake local dev services state (#795)
data/

# ── Node / TypeScript ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Appended to the language-neutral base by init-workspace.sh when a package.json
# marks the repo as Node/TypeScript.
#
# NOTE: no blanket `dist/` ignore — a JS GitHub Action commits its bundled
# entrypoint (dist/index.js, referenced by action.yml `runs.main`), so ignoring
# dist/ would silently drop the committed bundle (#1024).

# Dependencies
node_modules/

# TypeScript incremental build info
*.tsbuildinfo

# tsc/ncc emit .d.ts + .d.ts.map declaration byproducts under dist/src/ (#1092);
# the .d.ts.map files embed absolute file:// paths regenerated per checkout, so
# ignore them — WITHOUT a blanket dist/ ignore, keeping the committed bundle
# dist/index.js + dist/package.json tracked.
dist/src/

# Coverage reports
coverage/
.nyc_output/

# Repo-specific root .gitignore entries — yours to edit; upgrades never
# overwrite this file. This is the durable committed home for repo-ROOT ignores:
# git honors a root ignore only from the root .gitignore, which devkit
# regenerates on every upgrade, so entries added HERE are appended to that
# regenerated .gitignore and survive. Put durable repo-root ignores below (not
# in the managed .gitignore, where hand edits are lost).
#
# Flake-generated pre-commit config: this repo opts into flake-sourced hooks
# (`hooks = { }` in flake.nix), which installs .pre-commit-config.yaml as a
# /nix/store symlink. It must never be committed — the target is machine-local.
# (The #1092 auto-seed only fires when the store symlink is resolvable at
# scaffold time; a direnv-mode upgrade runs in a container without /nix/store,
# so it is pinned here in the durable consumer-owned ignore instead.)
.pre-commit-config.yaml

# Examples (uncomment / add your own):
#   /scratch/
#   /secrets.local.yaml
